§ 25-3-23 - DEVELOPMENT PLAN REQUIRED.
An applicant for a traditional neighborhood district shall prepare a Development Plan as part of the zoning application. The Development Plan must contain the
following information:
(1) locations and sizes of the Neighborhood Center Area, Mixed Residential Area, and, if applicable, Neighborhood Edge Area, Workshop Area, and
Employment Center Area;
(2) locations of major civic uses;
(3) locations of commercial uses in Mixed Residential Areas;
(4) layout of the transportation network for all modes of travel;
(5) locations and sizes of private open space and public open space;
